@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<section class="panel stack-lg">
    <span class="eyebrow">Privacy</span>
    <h1 class="headline-md">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="body-lg">Darwin Lingua uses account, learning, organizer, moderation, and operational data to run the language-learning service, protect users, and support account recovery.</p>
</section>

<section class="grid-two-col">
    <article class="panel stack-md">
        <h2 class="headline-sm">Account and learning data</h2>
        <ul class="feature-list">
            <li>Account email addresses are used for sign-in, email confirmation, password reset, security notifications, and support workflows.</li>
            <li>Learning preferences, favorites, recent activity, learner profiles, organizer claims, partner requests, RSVP records, and moderation reports are stored to provide requested product features.</li>
            <li>Admin and operator access is limited by role-based authorization and is used for support, moderation, publishing, diagnostics, and operational review.</li>
        </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="panel stack-md">
        <h2 class="headline-sm">Transactional emails</h2>
        <ul class="feature-list">
            <li>Darwin Lingua sends transactional emails for registration confirmation, password reset, email change, organizer claims, RSVP confirmations, partner-request outcomes, moderation alerts, and account security events.</li>
            <li>Transactional emails are not marketing emails and are not used for newsletters or promotional campaigns.</li>
            <li>Production and staging email delivery may be processed by an external email provider configured by the operator.</li>
        </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="panel stack-md">
        <h2 class="headline-sm">Email diagnostics</h2>
        <ul class="feature-list">
            <li>Delivery diagnostics store scenario, template, culture, provider, status, safe failure summaries, timestamps, and a hashed recipient email value.</li>
            <li>Reset tokens, confirmation tokens, full recovery links, and full magic links are not stored in delivery logs.</li>
            <li>Delivery logs are retained only for the configured operational retention period and can be cleaned up by authorized admins.</li>
        </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="panel stack-md">
        <h2 class="headline-sm">Provider and support processing</h2>
        <ul class="feature-list">
            <li>Email providers may process recipient email addresses, message metadata, and message content strictly to deliver transactional emails and report delivery status.</li>
            <li>Support contact addresses are monitored for account recovery and operational support.</li>
            <li>Before public production launch, the production email provider and any required data-processing agreement must be reviewed by the release owner.</li>
        </ul>
    </article>
</section>
